line/cline/10.3-access-control)\n-   [Authentication and Accounts](/cline/cline/11-authentication-and-accounts)\n-   [Authentication System](/cline/cline/11.1-authentication-system)\n-   [Account Service](/cline/cline/11.2-account-service)\n-   [Credits and Billing](/cline/cline/11.3-credits-and-billing)\n-   [Remote Configuration](/cline/cline/11.4-remote-configuration)\n-   [Banner and Feature Flag Systems](/cline/cline/11.5-banner-and-feature-flag-systems)\n-   [CLI Tool](/cline/cline/12-cli-tool)\n-   [CLI Architecture](/cline/cline/12.1-cli-architecture)\n-   [CLI Commands and Options](/cline/cline/12.2-cli-commands-and-options)\n-   [CLI Interactive Mode](/cline/cline/12.3-cli-interactive-mode)\n-   [CLI Headless Mode](/cline/cline/12.4-cli-headless-mode)\n-   [Agent Client Protocol (ACP)](/cline/cline/12.5-agent-client-protocol-\\(acp\\))\n-   [Cline SDK](/cline/cline/13-cline-sdk)\n-   [SDK Architecture and Packages](/cline/cline/13.1-sdk-architecture-and-packages)\n-   [Agent API and ClineCore](/cline/cline/13.2-agent-api-and-clinecore)\n-   [SDK Provider and Model Gateway](/cline/cline/13.3-sdk-provider-and-model-gateway)\n-   [Plugins and Extensions](/cline/cline/13.4-plugins-and-extensions)\n-   [Hub Daemon and Zen Mode](/cline/cline/13.5-hub-daemon-and-zen-mode)\n-   [Automation and Cron](/cline/cline/13.6-automation-and-cron)\n-   [SDK Examples and Connectors](/cline/cline/13.7-sdk-examples-and-connectors)\n-   [Development and Extensibility](/cline/cline/14-development-and-extensibility)\n-   [Build System and Protocol Buffers](/cline/cline/14.1-build-system-and-protocol-buffers)\n-   [Testing Infrastructure](/cline/cline/14.2-testing-infrastructure)\n-   [Telemetry System](/cline/cline/14.3-telemetry-system)\n-   [Feature Flags](/cline/cline/14.4-feature-flags)\n-   [Publishing and Release](/cline/cline/14.5-publishing-and-release)\n-   [Contributing Guidelines](/cline/cline/14.6-contributing-guidelines)\n-   [Glossary](/cline/cline/15-glossary)\n\nMenu\n\n# State and Storage\n\nRelevant source files\n\n-   [proto/cline/models.proto](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/proto/cline/models.proto)\n-   [proto/cline/state.proto](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/proto/cline/state.proto)\n-   [src/common.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/common.ts)\n-   [src/core/api/index.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/api/index.ts)\n-   [src/core/commands/reconstructTaskHistory.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/commands/reconstructTaskHistory.ts)\n-   [src/core/context/context-tracking/ContextTrackerTypes.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/context/context-tracking/ContextTrackerTypes.ts)\n-   [src/core/context/context-tracking/FileContextTracker.test.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/context/context-tracking/FileContextTracker.test.ts)\n-   [src/core/context/context-tracking/FileContextTracker.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/context/context-tracking/FileContextTracker.ts)\n-   [src/core/context/context-tracking/ModelContextTracker.test.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/context/context-tracking/ModelContextTracker.test.ts)\n-   [src/core/context/context-tracking/ModelContextTracker.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/context/context-tracking/ModelContextTracker.ts)\n-   [src/core/controller/state/updateSettings.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/controller/state/updateSettings.ts)\n-   [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts)\n-   [src/core/storage/disk.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/disk.ts)\n-   [src/core/storage/state-migrations.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/state-migrations.ts)\n-   [src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts)\n-   [src/shared/proto-conversions/models/api-configuration-conversion.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/shared/proto-conversions/models/api-configuration-conversion.ts)\n-   [src/shared/storage/state-keys.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/shared/storage/state-keys.ts)\n-   [src/test/cline-api.test.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/test/cline-api.test.ts)\n-   [webview-ui/src/components/settings/sections/FeatureSettingsSection.tsx](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/webview-ui/src/components/settings/sections/FeatureSettingsSection.tsx)\n-   [webview-ui/src/components/settings/sections/TerminalSettingsSection.tsx](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/webview-ui/src/components/settings/sections/TerminalSettingsSection.tsx)\n-   [webview-ui/src/components/settings/utils/providerUtils.ts](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/webview-ui/src/components/settings/utils/providerUtils.ts)\n\nThis document describes Cline's comprehensive state management and persistence system. The system manages application configuration, user settings, secrets, task-specific state, and remote enterprise configuration through a file-backed storage architecture with in-memory caching.\n\nFor details on the primary implementation, see [State Manager](/cline/cline/5.1-state-manager). For information about how state is communicated to the UI, see [WebView Communication](/cline/cline/2.4-webview-communication) and [gRPC Service Layer](/cline/cline/2.5-grpc-service-layer).\n\n---\n\n## Storage Architecture Overview\n\nCline uses a three-tier architecture for state management: disk storage, in-memory cache, and debounced persistence. All state is file-backed, enabling settings to persist across extension restarts and be shared across different interfaces (VS Code, CLI).\n\n### Three-Tier State Management\n\n**Sources:** [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts58-123](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L58-L123) [src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts22-86](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts#L22-L86) [src/core/storage/disk.ts30-42](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/disk.ts#L30-L42)\n\n### Code Entity Mapping: Storage Helpers\n\nThe following diagram maps the natural language concept of \"Reading State\" to the specific utility functions and constants used by the `StateManager` to interface with the disk.\n\n**Sources:** [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts141-143](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L141-L143) [src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts25-86](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts#L25-L86) [src/core/storage/disk.ts44-70](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/disk.ts#L44-L70) [src/core/storage/disk.ts27-29](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/disk.ts#L27-L29)\n\n---\n\n## State Manager\n\nThe `StateManager` is a singleton that provides centralized access to all application state with immediate reads from an in-memory cache and debounced, asynchronous writes to disk. It handles the distinction between global settings (e.g., API keys) and workspace-scoped state (e.g., rule toggles).\n\nFor details, see [State Manager](/cline/cline/5.1-state-manager).\n\n### Key Responsibilities\n\n-   **Caching**: Maintains `globalStateCache`, `taskStateCache`, and `secretsCache` for fast access [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts61-66](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L61-L66)\n-   **Model Caching**: Manages an in-memory `modelInfoCache` for dynamic providers like OpenRouter, Ollama, and Groq with a 1-hour TTL (`MODEL_CACHE_TTL_MS`) [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts75-104](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L75-L104)\n-   **Debouncing**: Batches updates using a `PERSISTENCE_DELAY_MS` (500ms) to prevent excessive disk I/O [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts107-112](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L107-L112)\n-   **Syncing**: Provides an `onSyncExternalChange` callback and `taskHistoryWatcher` to notify the UI when files are changed externally [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts113-120](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L113-L120)\n-   **Initialization**: Loads data from the file-backed `StorageContext` and populates the cache via `populateCache()` [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts128-161](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L128-L161)\n\n**Sources:** [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts58-168](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L58-L168)\n\n---\n\n## Disk Storage Organization\n\nCline organizes data into global storage and per-task storage. Global storage includes the main configuration, model caches, and MCP settings. Per-task storage maintains the specific conversation history and checkpoints for individual AI interactions.\n\nFor details, see [Disk Storage Organization](/cline/cline/5.2-disk-storage-organization).\n\n### Directory Layout\n\n-   **Global Files**: Defined in `GlobalFileNames`, including `globalState.json`, `cline_mcp_settings.json`, and model caches like `openrouter_models.json` [src/core/storage/disk.ts44-70](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/disk.ts#L44-L70)\n-   **Task Storage**: Located in `tasks/<taskId>/`, containing `api_conversation_history.json`, `ui_messages.json`, and `task_metadata.json` [src/core/storage/disk.ts44-47](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/disk.ts#L44-L47) [src/core/storage/disk.ts67](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/disk.ts#L67-L67)\n-   **Home Path**: Defaults to `~/.cline` across platforms via `getClineHomePath()` [src/core/storage/disk.ts117-119](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/disk.ts#L117-L119)\n-   **Atomic Writes**: The `atomicWriteFile` function uses a temp-and-rename pattern (temp file + `fs.rename`) to prevent partial data corruption [src/core/storage/disk.ts30-42](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/disk.ts#L30-L42)\n\n**Sources:** [src/core/storage/disk.ts44-123](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/disk.ts#L44-L123)\n\n---\n\n## Settings Precedence\n\nCline employs a layered settings model. Values are resolved by checking multiple sources in order: remote configuration (enterprise overrides), session overrides (CLI flags), task-level overrides, and finally global user settings.\n\nFor details, see [Settings Precedence](/cline/cline/5.3-settings-precedence).\n\n### Resolution Logic\n\nThe system distinguishes between Plan and Act modes, allowing separate API providers and models for each [src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts95-98](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts#L95-L98) Configuration is normalized via `normalizeApiConfiguration` which resolves the correct provider and model based on the active mode [webview-ui/src/components/settings/utils/providerUtils.ts180-185](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/webview-ui/src/components/settings/utils/providerUtils.ts#L180-L185) Conflict resolution during updates is handled by the `updateSettings` controller logic [src/core/controller/state/updateSettings.ts25-58](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/controller/state/updateSettings.ts#L25-L58)\n\nLayer\n\nSource\n\nPrecedence\n\nDescription\n\n**Remote**\n\n`remoteConfigCache`\n\nHighest\n\nEnterprise policies (e.g., `allowedMCPServers`) [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts64](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L64-L64)\n\n**Session**\n\n`sessionOverrideCache`\n\nHigh\n\nTemporary overrides for the current session [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts63](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L63-L63)\n\n**Task**\n\n`taskStateCache`\n\nMedium\n\nSettings specific to an active task [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts62](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L62-L62)\n\n**Global**\n\n`globalStateCache`\n\nLowest\n\nStandard user-defined settings [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts61](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L61-L61)\n\n**Sources:** [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts61-66](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L61-L66) [src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts93-107](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts#L93-L107) [webview-ui/src/components/settings/utils/providerUtils.ts180-243](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/webview-ui/src/components/settings/utils/providerUtils.ts#L180-L243) [src/core/controller/state/updateSettings.ts25-58](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/controller/state/updateSettings.ts#L25-L58)\n\n---\n\n## Secrets Management\n\nSensitive information such as API keys and OAuth tokens are stored separately from general settings. In VS Code, these are backed by `SecretStorage`; in the CLI, they are persisted to a restricted-access file via the `StorageContext`.\n\nFor details, see [Secrets Management](/cline/cline/5.4-secrets-management).\n\n### Implementation\n\n-   **Secret Access**: Managed via `StateManager.getSecret()` and `setSecret()`, ensuring credentials never leak into standard log files or global state JSON [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts316-339](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L316-L339)\n-   **Storage Mapping**: The `readSecretsFromStorage` helper iterates through `SecretKeys` defined in `state-keys.ts` to populate the in-memory cache from the secure store [src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts25-30](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts#L25-L30) [src/shared/storage/state-keys.ts12-14](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/shared/storage/state-keys.ts#L12-L14)\n-   **Proto Mapping**: Secrets are defined in the `Secrets` message in `state.proto` and `ModelsApiSecrets` in `models.proto` for secure transport across the gRPC layer [proto/cline/state.proto62-109](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/proto/cline/state.proto#L62-L109) [proto/cline/models.proto162-243](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/proto/cline/models.proto#L162-L243)\n\n**Sources:** [src/core/storage/StateManager.ts316-339](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/StateManager.ts#L316-L339) [src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts25-30](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/core/storage/utils/state-helpers.ts#L25-L30) [src/shared/storage/state-keys.ts12-14](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/src/shared/storage/state-keys.ts#L12-L14) [proto/cline/state.proto62-109](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/proto/cline/state.proto#L62-L109) [proto/cline/models.proto162-243](https://github.com/cline/cline/blob/8a6441fd/proto/cline/models.proto#L162-L243)\n\nDismiss\n\nRefresh this wiki\n\nEnter email to refresh\n\n### On this page\n\n-   [State and Storage](#state-and-storage)\n-   [Storage Architecture Overview](#storage-architecture-overview)\n-   [Three-Tier State Management](#three-tier-state-management)\n-   [Code Entity Mapping: Storage Helpers](#code-entity-mapping-storage-helpers)\n-   [State Manager](#state-manager)\n-   [Key Responsibilities](#key-responsibilities)\n-   [Disk Storage Organization](#disk-storage-organization)\n-   [Directory Layout](#directory-layout)\n-   [Settings Precedence](#settings-precedence)\n-   [Resolution Logic](#resolution-logic)\n-   [Secrets Management](#secrets-management)\n-   [Implementation](#implementation)",
