      "type": "answer",
      "text": "I now have comprehensive information from multiple authoritative sources. Here is a detailed summary of Cline's session storage format.\n\n---\n\n## Cline VS Code Extension -- Session Storage Format\n\n### 1. Where Session Data is Stored (File Paths)\n\nCline stores session data in VS Code's global storage directory. The exact path varies by operating system and IDE variant:\n\n**Primary Location (VS Code Extension):**\n\n| OS | Path |\n|---|---|\n| **macOS** | `~/Library/Application Support/Code/User/globalStorage/saoudrizwan.claude-dev/tasks/` |\n| **Linux** | `~/.config/Code/User/globalStorage/saoudrizwan.claude-dev/tasks/` |\n| **Windows** | `%APPDATA%\\Code\\User\\globalStorage\\saoudrizwan.claude-dev\\tasks\\` |\n\nNote: The extension ID `saoudrizwan.claude-dev` is the original name (\"Claude Dev\") before Cline rebranded.\n\n**Other IDE variants searched:**\n\n| IDE | Extension ID |\n|---|---|\n| VS Code Insiders | `Code - Insiders/User/globalStorage/saoudrizwan.claude-dev/` |\n| Cursor | `Cursor/User/globalStorage/saoudrizwan.claude-dev/` |\n| Windsurf | `Windsurf/User/globalStorage/saoudrizwan.claude-dev/` |\n| VS Code Server (Remote) | `~/.vscode-server/data/User/globalStorage/saoudrizwan.claude-dev/` |\n\n**Cline CLI storage:**\n- `~/.cline/data/tasks/` (cross-platform)\n\n**Global state and settings:**\n- `~/.cline/` is the cross-platform home directory for the CLI\n\nEach task gets a unique subdirectory under `tasks/` named by a ULID (timestamp-based unique identifier), e.g., `tasks/01HXyz123abc.../`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Storage Format\n\nCline uses **JSON files** -- not SQLite or JSONL for its primary session data. The format is plain JSON arrays and objects.\n\n**Key files per task directory:**\n\n| File | Format | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `ui_messages.json` | JSON array | Messages formatted for the Webview UI |\n| `api_conversation_history.json` | JSON array | Raw conversation history sent to/from LLM API |\n| `task_metadata.json` | JSON object | Files in context, model usage, environment history |\n| `context_history.json` | JSON | Context tracking history (file mentions evolution) |\n| `history_item.json` | JSON object | Per-task history item (token counts, timestamps, etc.) |\n\n**Global state files:**\n\n| File | Format | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `state/taskHistory.json` | JSON | Global task history index (all tasks) |\n| `settings/cline_mcp_settings.json` | JSON | MCP server configuration |\n| `cache/openrouter_models.json` | JSON | Cached OpenRouter model list |\n| `cache/mcp_marketplace_catalog.json` | JSON | MCP marketplace catalog cache |\n\n**SQLite usage:** Cline uses SQLite only for lock management (via `better-sqlite3`) and for Kilo Code's separate database -- NOT for primary session storage.\n\n**Atomic writes:** All file writes use an atomic temp-and-rename pattern (`fs.rename`) to prevent corruption.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Schema / Structure of Session Data\n\n#### `ui_messages.json` -- UI Message Schema\n\nEach entry is a `ClineRawMessage` object in a JSON array:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ts\": 1700000000000,        // Unix timestamp (milliseconds)\n  \"type\": \"say\" | \"ask\",      // Message type\n  \"say\": \"reasoning\" | \"api_req_started\" | \"api_req_finished\" | \"text\" | ...,\n  \"ask\": \"command\" | \"followup\" | ...,\n  \"text\": \"message content\",  // The main text content\n  \"reasoning\": \"...\",         // Reasoning/thinking content\n  \"images\": [\"base64...\"],    // Array of base64-encoded images\n  \"files\": [\"path/to/file\"],  // Array of file paths\n  \"partial\": false,           // Whether this is a partial/streaming message\n  \"modelInfo\": {              // Model information for this message\n    \"modelId\": \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\",\n    \"providerId\": \"anthropic\",\n    \"mode\": \"act\"             // \"plan\" or \"act\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### `api_conversation_history.json` -- API Conversation Schema\n\nEach entry is a `ClineApiMessage` object in a JSON array:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"msg_abc123\",         // Unique message ID\n  \"role\": \"user\" | \"assistant\",\n  \"content\": \"text\" | [       // String or array of content blocks\n    {\n      \"type\": \"text\",\n      \"text\": \"message content\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"thinking\",\n      \"thinking\": \"reasoning content\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"tool_use\",     // Tool call from assistant\n      \"id\": \"toolu_abc123\",\n      \"name\": \"write_to_file\",  // Tool name\n      \"input\": {              // Tool arguments (varies by tool)\n        \"path\": \"src/app.ts\",\n        \"content\": \"...\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"tool_result\",  // Tool result from user\n      \"tool_use_id\": \"toolu_abc123\",\n      \"content\": \"result text\",\n      \"is_error\": false\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ts\": 1700000000000,       // Timestamp\n  \"modelInfo\": {\n    \"modelId\": \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\",\n    \"providerId\": \"anthropic\",\n    \"mode\": \"act\"\n  },\n  \"metrics\": {}               // API usage metrics\n}\n```\n\n#### `task_metadata.json` -- Task Metadata Schema\n\n```json\n{\n  \"model_usage\": [            // Array of model usage records\n    {\n      \"modelId\": \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\",\n      \"tokensIn\": 5000,\n      \"tokensOut\": 2000,\n      \"cacheWrites\": 100,\n      \"cacheReads\": 300\n    }\n  ],\n  \"files_in_context\": [       // Files that were read/edited during task\n    {\n      \"path\": \"src/app.ts\",\n      \"lastKnownHash\": \"abc123\",\n      \"lastKnownModificationTime\": 1700000000000\n    }\n  ],\n  \"environment_history\": [...] // Environment/command execution history\n}\n```\n\n#### `taskHistory.json` / `history_item.json` -- Task History Schema\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"01HXyz123abc...\",   // Task ULID\n  \"ts\": 1700000000000,       // Creation timestamp\n  \"task\": \"Implement user authentication\",  // User's prompt/task description\n  \"tokensIn\": 50000,         // Total input tokens\n  \"tokensOut\": 20000,        // Total output tokens\n  \"cacheWrites\": 500,        // Cache write tokens\n  \"cacheReads\": 1500,        // Cache read tokens\n  \"cwdOnTaskInitialization\": \"/path/to/project\",  // Working directory\n  \"workspace\": \"/path/to/project\",\n  \"modelId\": \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\",\n  \"mode\": \"act\",             // \"plan\" or \"act\"\n  \"status\": \"completed\",     // Task status\n  \"apiConfigName\": \"default\" // API configuration name\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Available Fields Summary\n\n| Category | Fields Available |\n|---|---|\n| **Messages** | Text content, reasoning/thinking, timestamps, model info, partial/streaming state |\n| **Tool Calls** | Tool name, tool ID, input arguments, tool result content, success/error status |\n| **File Edits** | Files read/edited tracked in `files_in_context` with hash and modification time |\n| **Timestamps** | Per-message `ts` field, per-task creation time, context history timestamps |\n| **Token Usage** | `tokensIn`, `tokensOut`, `cacheWrites`, `cacheReads` at task level; per-model breakdown in `model_usage` |\n| **Images** | Base64-encoded images in `ui_messages.json` |\n| **Model Info** | `modelId`, `providerId`, `mode` (plan/act) per message |\n| **Task Metadata** | Model usage, files in context, environment/command history |\n| **Task History** | Task description, workspace path, status, API config name |\n\n---\n\n### Key Architectural Notes\n\n1. **All JSON, no SQLite for sessions:** Session data is stored as plain JSON files, not in a database. SQLite is only used for lock management.\n\n2. **Two parallel conversation stores:** `ui_messages.json` (for the UI) and `api_conversation_history.json` (for the LLM API) are separate files with different schemas but overlapping content.\n\n3. **Task ID = directory name:** Each task is a ULID-based directory under `tasks/`. The task ID is the directory name itself.\n\n4. **Global state via VS Code API:** Settings, API keys, and provider configurations are stored via VS Code's `globalState` API (backed by VS Code's internal SQLite database) and `secrets` API (backed by OS keychain), NOT as separate files.\n\n5. **Atomic writes:** All file persistence uses a temp-file-then-rename pattern to prevent data corruption.\n\n6. **Debounced persistence:** Writes are batched with a 500ms delay (`PERSISTENCE_DELAY_MS`) to prevent excessive disk I/O.",
